---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { name: 'Accessibility', href: '/accessibility/' }
];
---
<Base
  title="Accessibility | Muraqabah Initiative"
  description="Muraqabah Initiative's commitment to an accessible website, the standards we build toward, and how to reach us if you encounter a barrier."
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Accessibility" title="Accessibility statement" lede="Knowledge should be within everyone's reach. We build this website to be usable by as many people as possible, whatever tools they browse with." crumbs={crumbs} />

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose">
      <h2>Our commitment</h2>
      <p>
        Muraqabah Initiative aims to meet the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA across
        this website, and to keep improving as the site grows.
      </p>

      <h2>What we have built in</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML with a logical heading structure on every page</li>
        <li>A visible skip link and consistent keyboard navigation, including the mobile menu, accordions, and the gallery lightbox</li>
        <li>Text alternatives for meaningful images and decorative images marked accordingly</li>
        <li>Colour combinations chosen for readable contrast against our palette</li>
        <li>Form fields with proper labels, clear error messages, and status announcements for assistive technology</li>
        <li>Reduced-motion support: animations and counters are disabled when your system requests less motion</li>
        <li>Videos embedded with a click-to-play facade so nothing loads or moves without your action</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Known limitations</h2>
      <p>
        Some archival materials, such as event posters and PDF reports produced for print, may not be fully
        accessible. If you need the information they contain in another format, contact us and we will provide it.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party content</h2>
      <p>
        Donation and registration pages are hosted by Zeffy, and videos are hosted by YouTube. We choose partners
        with accessibility in mind, but their platforms are outside our direct control.
      </p>

      <h2>Tell us about a barrier</h2>
      <p>
        If any part of this website is difficult for you to use, we genuinely want to know. Email
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}> {site.email}</a> with the page address and a short description of the
        problem, and we will work to fix it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
